Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, possibly a krater or dinos; dark grey fabric containing mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The more pronounced curvature and thinner wall disassociates this sherd from British Museum 1965,0930.406-410, even if the lettering is equally large. Possibly from same vessel as 1888,0601.621.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.055)
